<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Adding a cell to a Jupyter notebook</b></p><p>You can add a new cell by one of the following ways:</p><ul ><li><p>Select <span class="control">Add Cell Above</span> or <span class="control">Add Cell Below</span> from the <span class="control">Cell</span> menu.</p></li><li><p>Click <span class="control">+</span> on the notebook toolbar.</p></li><li><p>Hover over a cell's top border to see the inline commands for adding a code cell and a Markdown cell. </p><p class="image"><img src="images/py_ds_add_cell.png" alt="Inline commands for adding cells" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></li></ul></body></html>